@user4 @user3 You can do it! And I'm happy to help you with my experiences.
Website: Take a look at @user5. It seems simple, looks good, and is OpenSource. I will switch one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: Take a look at cal.com. It's an Open-Source calendar service with integrations that allow you to schedule video calls with Element Call, JITSI, etc. Signal is also supported, but I haven't yet tested whether it works for messages or video calls.
I can recommend @user6. It offers end-to-end encryption, is decentralized, and Open Source.
